      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BUCKEYE (2) comes here with a fitness edge over the bulk of these and finds an easier contest today. Sat on the fast tempo with a courageous third to Journeyman over 1200m at Warwick Farm in a Super Maiden. Zac Lloyd sticks and expected to go close. DUCK FOR COVER (1) six-year-old gelding who made his debut with a tenacious on-pace fourth over 1200m at this track. Gets the right run and can come on strongly for this. CRUSADER VOYAGE (3) gelded over the break and looks set for a big campaign. Up quickly in class with a fading twelfth in the G1 Spring Champion over 2000m last October. Can sprint well fresh with the two trials under the belt. STORMING HOME (8) The Autumn Sun filly from Group winning mare White Moss on debut for the Archibald camp. Wasn't pushed out in the two trials and gets her chance from the low draw.",
